enhanced_by.reason: The 'increased' list must be set before calling 'isCoreChanged' to accurately determine if there are any required parameters that have increased.
The 'missing' list must be set before calling 'isCoreChanged' to accurately determine if there are any parameters that are missing.
Both 'isCoreChanged' and 'isChanged' methods evaluate the compatibility of changes, making 'isChanged' a good candidate for assertions related to 'isCoreChanged'.
The 'equals' method can be used to compare the state of 'ChangedParameters' objects before and after calling 'isCoreChanged' to verify if the core properties have changed.
